{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_WENAjVZ7ZvOPo4ZT9abd5upN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→Ticket: TST-001\n     3→Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     4→Status: READY\n     5→Updated: 2026-03-18\n     6→Owner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\n     7→PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n     8→Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\n     9→Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n    10→Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\n    11→Reports:\n    12→  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n    13→  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n    14→  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n    15→  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n    19→\n    20→> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n    21→> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n    24→Updated: 2026-03-18\n    25→Ticket: TST-001\n    26→Stage: tasklist\n    27→Status: READY\n    28→\n    29→### TL;DR\n    30→- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n    31→- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n    32→- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n    33→- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n    34→\n    35→### Scope & boundaries\n    36→- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n    37→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n    38→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n    39→  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n    40→  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n    41→  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n    42→  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n    43→- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n    44→  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n    45→  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n    46→  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n    47→  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n    48→- Integrations / dependencies:\n    49→  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n    50→  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n    51→  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n    52→  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n    53→\n    54→### Decisions & defaults (living)\n    55→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n    56→- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n    57→- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n    58→- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n    59→\n    60→### Test policy (iteration budget)\n    61→- Cadence: checkpoint\n    62→- Profile: targeted\n    63→- Tasks:\n    64→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n    65→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    66→- Filters:\n    67→  - `RbacWebFilterTest`\n    68→  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest`\n    69→  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n    70→- Budget minutes: 10\n    71→- Known flaky / failing: none\n    72→\n    73→### Commands quickstart (copy/paste)\n    74→- Format: cmd\n    75→- Tests (manual):\n    76→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*Rbac*\"`\n    77→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    78→- Run/Dev:\n    79→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:bootRun`\n    80→  - `npm run dev` (frontend)\n    81→- DB migration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n    82→\n    83→### Open questions / blockers\n    84→- None — all questions resolved via PRD decisions Q1-Q5\n    85→\n    86→### Blockers summary (handoff)\n    87→- None\n    88→\n    89→### References\n    90→- Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (OUTDATED — uses WebSocket, follow Plan for SSE)\n    91→- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md (Status: READY)\n    92→- Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n    93→- Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md (Status: READY, source of truth for implementation)\n    94→\n    95→---\n    96→\n    97→## AIDD:SPEC_PACK\n    98→Updated: 2026-03-18\n    99→Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (status: draft — OUTDATED)\n   100→\n   101→- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement on mutation APIs with auditable role operations and SSE-based frontend synchronization\n   102→- Non-goals:\n   103→  - UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n   104→  - Migration of historical access logs\n   105→  - Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n   106→  - WebSocket (Spec says WebSocket, but Plan uses SSE — follow Plan)\n   107→- Key decisions:\n   108→  - Backend: Custom WebFlux filter for RBAC (no Spring Security)\n   109→  - Auth: X-Profile-Key header-based identity extraction\n   110→  - Frontend: React + Zustand (not Redux as in Spec)\n   111→  - Session Sync: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — NOT WebSocket, NOT Polling\n   112→  - Cache: Caffeine with 5min TTL\n   113→  - Audit: PostgreSQL table `rbac_audit_log` with JSONB metadata\n   114→- Risks:\n   115→  - R-001: Profile service unavailable → Circuit breaker, fail-closed, cache roles\n   116→  - R-002: Cache stale roles after assignment → Cache invalidation on role change\n   117→  - R-003: SSE connection memory leak → Proper cleanup on disconnect\n   118→  - R-004: Audit log write failures → Async logging, error queue\n   119→  - R-005: RBAC filter performance degradation → Caffeine cache, async audit\n   120→  - R-006: Breaking change to existing APIs → Feature flags, audit-only mode first\n   121→  - R-007: Component scan misses RBAC beans → Add to all profile configs\n   122→  - R-008: Missing profile service integration → Define contract or implement local role storage\n   123→\n   124→## AIDD:TEST_STRATEGY\n   125→- Unit:\n   126→  - Scope: RBAC middleware logic, role caching, audit log formatting, useRoleGuard hook\n   127→  - Files: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n   128→- Integration:\n   129→  - Scope: RBAC filter + profile service client, audit log DB writes, SSE endpoint connection handling\n   130→  - Files: `RbacIntegrationTest`, `RoleEventsControllerTest`\n   131→- Contract:\n   132→  - Scope: API response schemas (403 format), SSE event format\n   133→  - Files: Contract tests for `/api/profiles/role-events` endpoint\n   134→- E2E/Stand:\n   135→  - Critical paths:\n   136→    - flow.admin-change-role: Admin assigns role → user receives SSE update\n   137→    - flow.unauthorized-access: User attempts restricted action → 403 + audit log\n   138→    - flow.live-session-update: Role change propagates to frontend within 5 seconds\n   139→- Test data:\n   140→  - Fixtures: Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions, regular user with limited role, user with missing headers\n   141→\n   142→---\n   143→\n   144→## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION\n   145→> Конкретные команды/фильтры запуска (execution‑уровень).\n   146→- profile: targeted\n   147→- tasks:\n   148→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n   149→  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n   150→  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacIntegrationTest*\"`\n   151→- filters:\n   152→  - `RbacWebFilterTest` — filter logic tests\n   153→  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest` — caching and role resolution tests\n   154→  - `AuditLogServiceTest` — audit logging tests\n   155→  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts` — frontend hook tests\n   156→- when: checkpoint\n   157→- reason: Fast feedback on RBAC module changes; full suite on PR\n   158→\n   159→---\n   160→\n   161→## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL\n   162→> Полный список итераций реализации (от 1 до N). Должен быть **детальнее плана** и не оставлять пробелов.\n   163→> Канонический формат итерации: `- [ ] I{N}: <title> (iteration_id: I{N})`\n   164→\n   165→- [ ] I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model (iteration_id: I1)\n   166→  - parent_iteration_id: none\n   167→  - Goal: Create database schema for audit logging and establish RBAC domain model\n   168→  - Outputs:\n   169→    - `db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` — migration for rbac_audit_log table\n   170→    - `Role.java` — Role enum (ADMIN, USER, VIEWER)\n   171→    - `ProfileIdentity.java` — Value object for namespace:reference\n   172→    - `Permission.java` — Permission enum (READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN)\n   173→    - `RbacDecision.java` — Decision record\n   174→    - `AuditLogEntity.java` — JPA entity for audit log\n   175→    - `AuditLogRepository.java` — Spring Data repository\n   176→  - DoD: Migration runs successfully, all domain classes compile with tests, repository can save/retrieve entries\n   177→  - Boundaries:\n   178→    - Only database and domain layer — no services or filters yet\n   179→    - Do not modify existing tables\n   180→  - Priority: high\n   181→  - Blocking: true\n   182→  - deps: []\n   183→  - locks: []\n   184→  - Expected paths:\n   185→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n   186→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/`\n   187→    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/`\n   188→  - Size budget:\n   189→    - max_files: 10\n   190→    - max_loc: 500\n   191→  - Commands:\n   192→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n   193→    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\"`\n   194→  - Exit criteria:\n   195→    - Migration applies without errors\n   196→    - Unit tests pass for doma