{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_E6QqOIz8DGnep5qflNY5SXvB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, after reviewing the project structure and comparing the spec with the tasklist, there's a clear contradiction regarding the synchronization mechanism. The spec explicitly calls for WebSocket integration at `/ws/session`, but the tasklist summary indicates SSE should be used, noting the spec is outdated. \n\nWait, the PRD further complicates this by suggesting a polling mechanism (Q5). This discrepancy is a major red flag; if I implement the wrong protocol, I'll have to refactor the connection logic later. I need to find the definitive architectural direction.\n\nActually, before I touch any code, I must look at the implementation plan. The plan should contain the final say on these technical choices and clarify whether the tasklist or the spec takes precedence. It will also likely contain the phased rollout strategy and specific acceptance criteria for the RBAC enforcement and audit logging features.\n\nUnless I understand the plan's structure, I can't effectively map out the database migrations or the middleware filters. I need to see how the team intended to break this down into iterations. Therefore, reading the plan document is the most logical next step to resolve these ambiguities and prepare for the implementation phase.","signature":""}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":41184,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":41184,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9b8ac5de-2be9-49f1-b88a-69f288598101","uuid":"40abefe8-47c0-46e7-8411-652c03b5785f"}
