{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_WM0RrS534yZQKqyriV8XhKky","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"tool_USrqCg7t7sge7BUBBUY3s8cb","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Implement I1 for TST-001","prompt":"You are the implementer agent for ticket TST-001, Iteration I1.\n\n## Task\nImplement Iteration I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model for the FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement feature.\n\n## Context Pack Summary\n- **Ticket**: TST-001\n- **Slug**: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n- **Iteration**: I1\n- **Goal**: Create database schema for audit logging and establish RBAC domain model\n- **Stack**: Spring WebFlux (backend), React + Zustand (frontend), PostgreSQL, Liquibase for migrations\n\n## Files to Create\n\n### Database Migration\nFile: `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n\nThis migration creates the `rbac_audit_log` table with these columns:\n- id: UUID PK (gen_random_uuid())\n- timestamp: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE (default now())\n- actor_namespace: VARCHAR(32) NOT NULL\n- actor_reference: VARCHAR(128) NOT NULL\n- action: VARCHAR(32) NOT NULL (values: ACCESS, DENIED, GRANT, REVOKE)\n- target_resource: VARCHAR(256)\n- target_profile_namespace: VARCHAR(32)\n- target_profile_reference: VARCHAR(128)\n- result: VARCHAR(16) NOT NULL\n- http_method: VARCHAR(8)\n- http_path: VARCHAR(512)\n- metadata: JSONB\n\nIndexes to create:\n- idx_rbac_audit_timestamp on timestamp\n- idx_rbac_audit_actor on (actor_namespace, actor_reference)\n\n### Domain Classes\n\n1. **Role.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java`\n   - Enum with values: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER\n   \n2. **ProfileIdentity.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java`\n   - Record with namespace (String) and reference (String)\n   - Constructor validation: both fields required, non-null\n   - toString() format: \"namespace:reference\"\n   \n3. **Permission.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java`\n   - Enum with values: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN\n   \n4. **RbacDecision.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java`\n   - Record with allowed (boolean) and reason (String, nullable)\n   - Static factory methods: allowed(), denied(String reason)\n\n### Persistence Layer\n\n5. **AuditLogEntity.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n   - JPA entity mapping to rbac_audit_log table\n   - All fields from the migration\n   - Proper getters/setters\n   \n6. **AuditLogRepository.java** - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n   - Spring Data JPA repository\n   - Method: findByActorNamespaceAndActorReference(String, String, Pageable)\n   - Method: findByTimestampBetween(Instant, Instant, Pageable)\n\n### Tests\n\n7. **RoleTest.java** - `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RoleTest.java`\n   - Test enum values exist\n   \n8. **ProfileIdentityTest.java** - `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentityTest.java`\n   - Test construction, validation, toString\n   \n9. **AuditLogRepositoryTest.java** - `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepositoryTest.java`\n   - Test saving and retrieving audit log entries\n   - Use @DataJpaTest\n\n## Important Notes\n- Do NOT use Spring Security - the project uses custom WebFlux filters\n- Do NOT modify existing tables - only create new rbac_audit_log table\n- Use existing patterns from the codebase (check backend-mcp structure)\n- Follow existing package naming conventions\n- Make sure all tests compile and pass\n\n## Exit Criteria\n- Migration file created and follows Liquibase format\n- All domain classes compile\n- All persistence classes compile\n- Repository test passes\n- No existing code is broken\n\nPlease implement all these files. After creating them, run the tests to verify everything works.","subagent_type":"feature-dev-aidd:implementer"}}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":56101,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":56101,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9b8ac5de-2be9-49f1-b88a-69f288598101","uuid":"f37826cd-e256-406a-b1d0-103d6e44f118"}
