{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_dJ9SzK0ofwxpBa84wfDSBKtQ","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9b8ac5de-2be9-49f1-b88a-69f288598101","uuid":"6d8cddea-bc72-4f6b-b95c-4c4a0a85bc52","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md","oldString":"## AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG\n> Мини‑лог: фиксируй кратко, обновляй после каждой итерации.\n> Формат записи:\n> `- YYYY-MM-DD source=implement id=I4 kind=iteration hash=abc123 link=aidd/reports/tests/<ticket>/TST-001.jsonl msg=short-note`\n\n- (empty)","newString":"## AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG\n> Мини‑лог: фиксируй кратко, обновляй после каждой итерации.\n> Формат записи:\n> `- YYYY-MM-DD source=implement id=I4 kind=iteration hash=abc123 link=aidd/reports/tests/<ticket>/TST-001.jsonl msg=short-note`\n\n- 2026-03-18 source=implement id=I1 kind=iteration hash=a1f45f2 link=aidd/reports/loops/TST-001/I1 msg=\"Database migration + RBAC domain model complete. 10 files created, tests pass.\"","originalFile":"---\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\nStatus: READY\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nOwner: backend-lead, frontend-lead\nPRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\nPlan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\nResearch: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\nReports:\n  tests: aidd/reports/tests/TST-001/TST-001.jsonl\n  review_report: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.json\n  reviewer_marker: aidd/reports/reviewer/TST-001/TST-001.tests.json\n  qa: aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json\n---\n\n# Tasklist: TST-001 — FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n> Единственный источник правды для implement/review/qa.\n> Всегда начинайте чтение с `## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:SPEC_PACK`, затем `## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION`, затем `## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL`, затем `## AIDD:NEXT_3`.\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nStage: tasklist\nStatus: READY\n\n### TL;DR\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement for mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and SSE-based frontend role sync\n- Current focus (1 checkbox): I1 - Database migration + RBAC domain model\n- Done since last pack: PRD finalized, Plan created with 5 phases, research findings integrated\n- Risk level: medium — SSE infrastructure exists but profile service integration needs verification\n\n### Scope & boundaries\n- Allowed paths (patch boundaries):\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/` (new package)\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/` (migrations)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n  - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n  - `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n- Forbidden / out-of-scope:\n  - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/` — no changes to note domain\n  - `frontend/src/pages/notes/` — no changes to note UI\n  - Spring Security integration — using custom WebFlux filters\n  - WebSocket — using existing SSE infrastructure instead\n- Integrations / dependencies:\n  - Profile service API — fetch roles by namespace:reference (fallback to local DB if unavailable)\n  - PostgreSQL — rbac_audit_log table\n  - Caffeine cache — role caching with 5min TTL\n  - SSE endpoint — extends existing flow events infrastructure\n\n### Decisions & defaults (living)\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false), `rbac.audit-only` (default: true for Phase 1)\n- Contract/API: X-Profile-Key header format `namespace:reference`, X-Profile-Auth for verification\n- Data model changes: New `rbac_audit_log` table with JSONB metadata\n- Observability: Micrometer timer on RBAC filter, Caffeine cache stats, SSE connection metrics\n\n### Test policy (iteration budget)\n- Cadence: checkpoint\n- Profile: targeted\n- Tasks:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Filters:\n  - `RbacWebFilterTest`\n  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest`\n  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Budget minutes: 10\n- Known flaky / failing: none\n\n### Commands quickstart (copy/paste)\n- Format: cmd\n- Tests (manual):\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*Rbac*\"`\n  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n- Run/Dev:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:bootRun`\n  - `npm run dev` (frontend)\n- DB migration: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n\n### Open questions / blockers\n- None — all questions resolved via PRD decisions Q1-Q5\n\n### Blockers summary (handoff)\n- None\n\n### References\n- Spec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (OUTDATED — uses WebSocket, follow Plan for SSE)\n- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md (Status: READY)\n- Research: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n- Plan: aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md (Status: READY, source of truth for implementation)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:SPEC_PACK\nUpdated: 2026-03-18\nSpec: aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml (status: draft — OUTDATED)\n\n- Goal: Implement live RBAC enforcement on mutation APIs with auditable role operations and SSE-based frontend synchronization\n- Non-goals:\n  - UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\n  - Migration of historical access logs\n  - Multi-tenant RBAC scope\n  - WebSocket (Spec says WebSocket, but Plan uses SSE — follow Plan)\n- Key decisions:\n  - Backend: Custom WebFlux filter for RBAC (no Spring Security)\n  - Auth: X-Profile-Key header-based identity extraction\n  - Frontend: React + Zustand (not Redux as in Spec)\n  - Session Sync: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — NOT WebSocket, NOT Polling\n  - Cache: Caffeine with 5min TTL\n  - Audit: PostgreSQL table `rbac_audit_log` with JSONB metadata\n- Risks:\n  - R-001: Profile service unavailable → Circuit breaker, fail-closed, cache roles\n  - R-002: Cache stale roles after assignment → Cache invalidation on role change\n  - R-003: SSE connection memory leak → Proper cleanup on disconnect\n  - R-004: Audit log write failures → Async logging, error queue\n  - R-005: RBAC filter performance degradation → Caffeine cache, async audit\n  - R-006: Breaking change to existing APIs → Feature flags, audit-only mode first\n  - R-007: Component scan misses RBAC beans → Add to all profile configs\n  - R-008: Missing profile service integration → Define contract or implement local role storage\n\n## AIDD:TEST_STRATEGY\n- Unit:\n  - Scope: RBAC middleware logic, role caching, audit log formatting, useRoleGuard hook\n  - Files: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`, `useRoleGuard.test.ts`\n- Integration:\n  - Scope: RBAC filter + profile service client, audit log DB writes, SSE endpoint connection handling\n  - Files: `RbacIntegrationTest`, `RoleEventsControllerTest`\n- Contract:\n  - Scope: API response schemas (403 format), SSE event format\n  - Files: Contract tests for `/api/profiles/role-events` endpoint\n- E2E/Stand:\n  - Critical paths:\n    - flow.admin-change-role: Admin assigns role → user receives SSE update\n    - flow.unauthorized-access: User attempts restricted action → 403 + audit log\n    - flow.live-session-update: Role change propagates to frontend within 5 seconds\n- Test data:\n  - Fixtures: Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions, regular user with limited role, user with missing headers\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION\n> Конкретные команды/фильтры запуска (execution‑уровень).\n- profile: targeted\n- tasks:\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac.*\"`\n  - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n  - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacIntegrationTest*\"`\n- filters:\n  - `RbacWebFilterTest` — filter logic tests\n  - `ProfileRoleServiceTest` — caching and role resolution tests\n  - `AuditLogServiceTest` — audit logging tests\n  - `useRoleGuard.test.ts` — frontend hook tests\n- when: checkpoint\n- reason: Fast feedback on RBAC module changes; full suite on PR\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ITERATIONS_FULL\n> Полный список итераций реализации (от 1 до N). Должен быть **детальнее плана** и не оставлять пробелов.\n> Канонический формат итерации: `- [ ] I{N}: <title> (iteration_id: I{N})`\n\n- [x] I1: Database migration + RBAC domain model (iteration_id: I1) (link: commit-a1f45f2)\n  - parent_iteration_id: none\n  - Goal: Create database schema for audit logging and establish RBAC domain model\n  - Outputs:\n    - `db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` — migration for rbac_audit_log table\n    - `Role.java` — Role enum (ADMIN, USER, VIEWER)\n    - `ProfileIdentity.java` — Value object for namespace:reference\n    - `Permission.java` — Permission enum (READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN)\n    - `RbacDecision.java` — Decision record\n    - `AuditLogEntity.java` — JPA entity for audit log\n    - `AuditLogRepository.java` — Spring Data repository\n  - DoD: Migration runs successfully, all domain classes compile with tests, repository can save/retrieve entries\n  - Boundaries:\n    - Only database and domain layer — no services or filters yet\n    - Do not modify existing tables\n  - Priority: high\n  - Blocking: true\n  - deps: []\n  - locks: []\n  - Expected paths:\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/`\n  - Size budget:\n    - max_files: 10\n    - max_loc: 500\n  - Commands:\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:liquibaseUpdate`\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\"`\n  - Exit criteria:\n    - Migration applies without errors\n    - Unit tests pass for domain classes\n    - Repository integration test passes\n  - Steps:\n    - Create Liquibase changelog for rbac_audit_log table with indexes\n    - Create Role enum with standard roles\n    - Create ProfileIdentity value object with validation\n    - Create Permission enum\n    - Create RbacDecision record\n    - Create AuditLogEntity JPA entity\n    - Create AuditLogRepository interface\n    - Write unit tests for domain classes\n    - Write repository integration test\n  - Tests:\n    - profile: targeted\n    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLog*\" --tests \"*Role*\"`\n    - filters: `AuditLogRepositoryTest`, `RoleTest`\n  - Acceptance mapping: AC-2 (audit log structure)\n  - Risks & mitigations:\n    - Migration conflicts with existing schema → Use separate rbac changelog file\n    - JSONB type not supported → Verify PostgreSQL version compatibility\n  - Dependencies: PostgreSQL database, Liquibase\n\n- [ ] I2: RBAC WebFilter + Audit logging service (iteration_id: I2)\n  - parent_iteration_id: I1\n  - Goal: Implement RBAC WebFlux filter for mutation API protection and async audit logging\n  - Outputs:\n    - `RbacWebFilter.java` — Main RBAC filter (Order: HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100)\n    - `AuditLogService.java` — Async audit logging service\n    - `RbacPathMatcher.java` — Path matching logic for protected routes\n    - `RbacProperties.java` — Configuration properties\n    - `RbacConfiguration.java` — Spring configuration\n  - DoD: Filter intercepts POST/PUT/DELETE, returns 403 for unauthorized, audit log entries written, config loaded\n  - Boundaries:\n    - No profile service integration yet — use mock/stub\n    - No caching yet\n    - Do not modify existing controllers\n  - Priority: high\n  - Blocking: true\n  - deps: [I1]\n  - locks: []\n  - Expected paths:\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/`\n  - Size budget:\n    - max_files: 8\n    - max_loc: 800\n  - Commands:\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilterTest*\"`\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*AuditLogServiceTest*\"`\n  - Exit criteria:\n    - Filter unit tests pass with mocked role service\n    - Audit log service writes entries asynchronously\n    - 403 responses returned for unauthorized mutation requests\n    - Configuration properties load correctly\n  - Steps:\n    - Create RbacProperties configuration record\n    - Create RbacConfiguration Spring config\n    - Create RbacPathMatcher for protected path patterns\n    - Create AuditLogService with async executor\n    - Create RbacWebFilter with identity extraction\n    - Implement 403 response for denied access\n    - Write unit tests for filter with mocked dependencies\n    - Write integration test for audit logging\n  - Tests:\n    - profile: targeted\n    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RbacWebFilter*\" --tests \"*AuditLogService*\"`\n    - filters: `RbacWebFilterTest`, `AuditLogServiceTest`\n  - Acceptance mapping: AC-1 (403 responses), AC-2 (audit logging)\n  - Risks & mitigations:\n    - Filter ordering conflicts → Use Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100\n    - Async audit log failures → Error handling in executor\n  - Dependencies: I1\n\n- [ ] I3: Profile service integration + Role caching (iteration_id: I3)\n  - parent_iteration_id: I2\n  - Goal: Connect to profile service for role resolution with Caffeine caching\n  - Outputs:\n    - `ProfileClient.java` — WebClient for profile service\n    - `ProfileResponse.java` — Profile DTO\n    - `ProfileRoleService.java` — Role resolution with caching\n    - `RbacConfig.java` — Component scan configuration\n  - DoD: Profile client fetches roles, Caffeine cache with 5min TTL, cache invalidation works, fail-closed on errors\n  - Boundaries:\n    - No SSE events yet\n    - Profile service URL configurable\n  - Priority: high\n  - Blocking: true\n  - deps: [I2]\n  - locks: []\n  - Expected paths:\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n  - Size budget:\n    - max_files: 6\n    - max_loc: 400\n  - Commands:\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleServiceTest*\"`\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileClientTest*\"`\n  - Exit criteria:\n    - Profile client successfully fetches roles\n    - Cache hit rate > 90% under load\n    - P95 latency < 10ms with cache\n    - Graceful fallback when service unavailable\n  - Steps:\n    - Create ProfileResponse DTO\n    - Create ProfileClient with WebClient\n    - Create ProfileRoleService with Caffeine cache\n    - Implement cache invalidation method\n    - Create RbacConfig for component scanning\n    - Write unit tests for caching behavior\n    - Write integration tests for profile client\n    - Add cache metrics exposure\n  - Tests:\n    - profile: targeted\n    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*ProfileRoleService*\" --tests \"*ProfileClient*\"`\n    - filters: `ProfileRoleServiceTest`, `ProfileClientTest`\n  - Acceptance mapping: AC-4 (P95 ≤ 10ms)\n  - Risks & mitigations:\n    - Profile service unavailable → Fail-closed with empty roles\n    - Cache stale data → TTL 5min + explicit invalidation\n  - Dependencies: I2\n\n- [ ] I4: Frontend SSE integration + useRoleGuard hook (iteration_id: I4)\n  - parent_iteration_id: I3\n  - Goal: Implement frontend role synchronization via SSE and role guard hook\n  - Outputs:\n    - `useRoleGuard.ts` — React hook for role checking with SSE\n    - `RoleGuard.tsx` — Component for conditional rendering by role\n    - Updated `profileStore.ts` — SSE subscription and roleVersion\n  - DoD:\n    - useRoleGuard subscribes to SSE on mount\n    - Zustand store updates on role-change events\n    - RoleGuard component conditionally renders children\n    - AdminRoles page uses useRoleGuard hook\n  - Boundaries:\n    - No backend SSE endpoint yet — mock for testing\n    - Minimal changes to existing components\n  - Priority: high\n  - Blocking: true\n  - deps: [I3]\n  - locks: []\n  - Expected paths:\n    - `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts`\n    - `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx`\n    - `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n  - Size budget:\n    - max_files: 4\n    - max_loc: 300\n  - Commands:\n    - `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    - `npm test -- RoleGuard`\n  - Exit criteria:\n    - Hook tests pass\n    - Component renders correctly with/without role\n    - Store updates trigger re-renders\n    - Refactored AdminRoles works as before\n  - Steps:\n    - Add roleVersion and SSE subscription to profileStore\n    - Create useRoleGuard hook with memoized checks\n    - Create RoleGuard component with fallback support\n    - Refactor AdminRoles to use useRoleGuard\n    - Write tests for useRoleGuard hook\n    - Write tests for RoleGuard component\n  - Tests:\n    - profile: targeted\n    - tasks: `npm test -- useRoleGuard`\n    - filters: `useRoleGuard.test.ts`, `RoleGuard.test.tsx`\n  - Acceptance mapping: AC-3 (5s sync)\n  - Risks & mitigations:\n    - SSE connection errors → Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff\n    - Memory leaks on unmount → Proper cleanup in useEffect\n  - Dependencies: I3\n\n- [ ] I5: SSE endpoint + Role events (iteration_id: I5)\n  - parent_iteration_id: I4\n  - Goal: Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications and role assignment service\n  - Outputs:\n    - `RoleEventService.java` — SSE event management with Sinks\n    - `RoleEventsController.java` — SSE endpoint controller\n    - `RoleAssignmentService.java` — Role assignment with notifications\n  - DoD:\n    - SSE endpoint at `/api/profiles/role-events`\n    - Role change events broadcast to subscribers\n    - RoleAssignmentService notifies on GRANT/REVOKE\n    - Heartbeat every 30 seconds\n  - Boundaries:\n    - No authentication on SSE endpoint yet (public for now)\n    - In-memory subscription map (no Redis)\n  - Priority: medium\n  - Blocking: false\n  - deps: [I4]\n  - locks: []\n  - Expected paths:\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/`\n    - `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/`\n  - Size budget:\n    - max_files: 5\n    - max_loc: 400\n  - Commands:\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEventsController*\"`\n    - `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEventService*\"`\n  - Exit criteria:\n    - SSE endpoint returns event stream\n    - Role changes trigger notifications\n    - Subscribers receive updates within 5 seconds\n    - Proper cleanup on disconnect\n  - Steps:\n    - Create RoleEventService with Sinks.Many\n    - Create RoleEventsController with SSE producer\n    - Create RoleAssignmentService\n    - Integrate notification on role change\n    - Add heartbeat flux\n    - Write integration tests for SSE\n    - Write tests for role assignment notifications\n  - Tests:\n    - profile: targeted\n    - tasks: `./gradlew :backend-mcp:test --tests \"*RoleEvent*\"`\n    - filters: `RoleEventsControllerTest`, `RoleEventServiceTest`\n  - Acceptance mapping: AC-3, AC-2\n  - Risks & mitigations:\n    - Memory leak from subscriptions → Cleanup on cancel/terminate\n    - Too many concurrent connections → Subscriber limits\n  - Dependencies: I4\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:NEXT_3\n> 3 ближайших implement‑чекбокса. Pointer list: 1–2 строки и `ref:` на детализацию.\n- archived: (ref: iteration_id=I1) (done: 2026-03-18)\n- [ ] I2: RBAC WebFilter + Audit logging service (ref: iteration_id=I2)\n- [ ] I3: Profile service integration + Role caching (ref: iteration_id=I3)\n## AIDD:OUT_OF_SCOPE_BACKLOG\n> Побочные идеи/задачи, которые НЕ входят в текущий work_item (без расширения scope).\n- [ ] Redis distributed cache for roles (source: research)\n- [ ] WebSocket alternative to SSE (source: spec)\n- [ ] Admin UI for role management (source: prd)\n- [ ] Audit log retention automation (source: plan)\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:HANDOFF_INBOX\n> Сюда падают задачи из Research/Review/QA (с source: aidd/reports/...).\n\n\n---\n\n<!-- handoff:manual start -->\n<!-- handoff:manual end -->\n## AIDD:QA_TRACEABILITY\n> AC → check → result → evidence.\n- AC-1 -> <check> -> not-verified -> TBD\n- AC-2 -> <check> -> not-verified -> TBD\n- AC-3 -> <check> -> not-verified -> TBD\n- AC-4 -> <check> -> not-verified -> TBD\n## AIDD:CHECKLIST\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_SPEC\n- [x] PRD: Status READY (и нет незакрытых blocker вопросов)\n- [x] Research: Status reviewed\n- [x] Plan: существует и валиден\n- [x] Review Spec: Plan Review READY + PRD Review READY\n- [ ] Spec interview (optional): spec обновлён; затем `/feature-dev-aidd:tasks-new` для синхронизации tasklist\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_IMPLEMENT\n- [ ] Реализован функционал для checkbox #1 из AIDD:NEXT_3\n- [ ] Добавлены/обновлены тесты по плану\n- [ ] Обновлён AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK (scope + test policy)\n- [ ] Обновлён AIDD:TEST_EXECUTION (если менялась тестовая тактика)\n- [ ] Прогресс отмечен (см. AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG)\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_REVIEW\n- [ ] Reviewer: замечания добавлены в tasklist (handoff)\n- [ ] Требуемость тестов выставлена (если используете reviewer marker)\n- [ ] Изменения соответствуют plan/PRD (нет лишнего)\n\n### AIDD:CHECKLIST_QA\n- [ ] QA: AIDD:ACCEPTANCE проверены (traceability)\n- [ ] QA report сохранён (aidd/reports/qa/TST-001.json)\n- [ ] Known issues задокументированы\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG\n> Мини‑лог: фиксируй кратко, обновляй после каждой итерации.\n> Формат записи:\n> `- YYYY-MM-DD source=implement id=I4 kind=iteration hash=abc123 link=aidd/reports/tests/<ticket>/TST-001.jsonl msg=short-note`\n\n- (empty)\n## AIDD:HOW_TO_UPDATE\n- Правило итерации: **1 чекбокс** (или 2 тесно связанных) — затем Stop.\n- Отмечайте чекбоксы так:\n  - `- [x] I{N}: <title> (iteration_id: I{N}) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n  - `- [x] <handoff title> (id: review:F6) (link: <commit/pr|report>)`\n- После каждого [x] обновляй `AIDD:NEXT_3` (pointer list) и добавляй запись в `AIDD:PROGRESS_LOG`.\n- Если меняешь тестовый профиль/команды — обнови `AI